  <section id="faq" class="container-wide py-20">
    <span class="eyebrow">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text sm:text-4xl">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl divide-y divide-[var(--line)]">

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What do AI visibility tracking tools actually measure?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">AI visibility tracking tools measure whether and how often your brand, products, or content appear in AI-generated answers. Specifically, they submit a library of target prompts to AI platforms such as ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, and Copilot, then record citation frequency, brand mention rate, which URLs are cited, how your brand is described, and how competitor presence compares for the same queries. The output is a statistical picture of your AI answer presence rather than a rank position.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How is AI visibility tracking different from traditional rank tracking?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">Traditional rank trackers record a deterministic position — your page ranks number three for a given keyword. AI visibility trackers record a probabilistic presence — your brand was cited in 41% of responses to a given prompt category. This is a fundamentally different measurement model because generative AI outputs vary with each query. Visibility trackers handle this by running multiple samples per prompt and reporting aggregate citation rates, not fixed positions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Which AI platforms should a visibility tracker cover?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">At minimum: ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google Gemini, and Microsoft Copilot. These four platforms account for the large majority of consumer AI answer queries. Coverage of Google AI Overviews, Anthropic Claude, and Meta AI is a useful addition for brands that need comprehensive market coverage. The best tools also allow you to define your own prompt library so you can track the specific queries your audience actually uses.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How frequently should AI visibility data be refreshed?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">For most programmes, weekly tracking provides sufficient resolution to detect meaningful changes in citation frequency. Daily tracking is valuable for brands running active optimisation campaigns or responding to reputational events. The key requirement is consistency: the same prompts, the same platforms, and the same sample size per reporting period, so that trend lines reflect genuine change rather than sampling variation. Monthly snapshots are the minimum useful frequency.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Can AI visibility tools track how my brand is described, not just whether it appears?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">Yes, the better platforms capture the full text of AI responses alongside citation flags and brand mention data. This allows you to audit how AI models describe your brand's products, positioning, and expertise — and to identify cases where the description is outdated, inaccurate, or inconsistent with your current messaging. This qualitative layer is distinct from citation frequency metrics and is increasingly supported by leading visibility tracking platforms.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-5 text-left font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink-100 hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Are there free AI visibility tracking tools worth using?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon ml-4 h-5 w-5 shrink-0 text-ink-500 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M10 5a1 1 0 011 1v3h3a1 1 0 110 2h-3v3a1 1 0 11-2 0v-3H6a1 1 0 110-2h3V6a1 1 0 011-1z"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300" style="max-height:0">
          <p class="pb-5 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">Several platforms offer limited free tiers that provide genuine value for establishing an initial baseline. Manual spot-checking across AI platforms at no cost, limited prompt queries per month on entry-tier paid plans, and trial periods are all worth using to orient your programme. For a systematic programme requiring custom prompt libraries and historical data retention, a paid tool is necessary. Free tiers are best used for orientation, not ongoing tracking.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

